item.description:
&lt;p&gt;Vybz Kartel drops his new street-wise ganja anthem &lt;em&gt;Nawmal Again&lt;/em&gt; - a big tune for all the herbalists.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We spin back to 1983 with Wayne Smith’s &lt;em&gt;Smoker Super&lt;/em&gt; - freshly reissued on VP Records, showcasing the early digital stylings that changed dancehall forever.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And five golden era Studio One 7&quot;s, pressed fresh from the original master tapes - Winston Matthews, Sound Dimension, Merlene Webber and more, true foundation sounds!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For years, Roberto Sánchez has stood among &lt;strong&gt;Riddim Yard’s top producers&lt;/strong&gt; – a master of live-tape, analogue roots reggae whose A-Lone Ark Muzik Studio in Santander keeps the spirit of the 70s alive. But it’s not just his mixing board skills – &lt;strong&gt;his vocal work and harmony arrangements have long been a Riddim Yard favourite&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now he steps forward on the mic with &lt;em&gt;Singers &amp;amp; Players&lt;/em&gt; – nine conscious and spiritual songs voiced over heavyweight riddims from his own band &lt;strong&gt;Message&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another crew that gets regular rotation on Riddim Yard, the French sound system collective &lt;strong&gt;Stand High Patrol&lt;/strong&gt; return with &lt;em&gt;Underground Oasis&lt;/em&gt; – a deep, dubbed-out journey that blends roots and electronic textures in their unmistakably fresh, original and creative style. Forever pushing the boundaries of modern dub while keeping the culture at the core.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Plus new Afrobeats from Burna Boy off the back of his first ever Australian show in Melbourne last night.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand new European releases from some Riddim Yard favourites.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A new 7-inch from one of Riddim Yard’s favourite reggae crews. On &lt;em&gt;Troubled World&lt;/em&gt;, world-class rub-a-dub singer &lt;strong&gt;Peter Youthman&lt;/strong&gt; steps forward with a powerful vocal cut produced by William Spring for his consistently killer &lt;strong&gt;Roll &amp;amp; Record&lt;/strong&gt; label in &lt;strong&gt;France.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Plus killer rocksteady revival from Riddim Yard favourites &lt;strong&gt;Adubta and Marcus I&lt;/strong&gt;. Think vintage rocksteady with a twist of Lee &#x27;Scratch&#x27; Perry Black Ark. Fire from Europe!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also in the mix: &lt;strong&gt;A Wicked Combination - Fruits Records &amp;amp; Roberto Sánchez in Dub Style. &lt;/strong&gt;Spanish engineer Roberto Sánchez has long been one of the top producers featured on the show, and Swiss label Fruits Records is one of the finest labels in modern roots and dub. Roberto mixed the original vocal cuts himself years back, and now he’s taken those same sessions and turned them into a full dub showcase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Buju Banton&lt;/strong&gt; is back to his best on a rugged brand new dancehall shot &lt;strong&gt;Hard Ears&lt;/strong&gt; on Gargamel Music.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, a deep crate gem out of &lt;strong&gt;Boston Massachusetts&lt;/strong&gt; - rare 80s roots from &lt;strong&gt;Healin’ Of The Nations&lt;/strong&gt;, a cult-status band whose indie pressings became treasured by roots collectors worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Plus some foundation cuts in the mix: classic rocksteady from &lt;strong&gt;The Hamlins&lt;/strong&gt; at &lt;strong&gt;Studio One&lt;/strong&gt;, sweet harmonies and timeless Coxsone magic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Three fresh cuts from one of Riddim Yard&#x27;s favourite modern dancehall artists, the ever-prolific &lt;strong&gt;Chronic Law&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;em&gt;Rumours&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;Big A&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Rich Inna Farin&lt;/em&gt; bringing that signature Law Boss energy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Heavyweight roots selections from &lt;strong&gt;Yabby You&lt;/strong&gt; with Jamaican saxophone king &lt;strong&gt;Tommy McCook&lt;/strong&gt;, drawing from the classic &lt;em&gt;Blazing Horns&lt;/em&gt; album.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Plus deep cultural fire from &lt;strong&gt;Burning Spear&lt;/strong&gt;, featuring two powerful tracks off his 1980 album &lt;em&gt;Hail H.I.M.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;War season continues as the feud between Tommy Lee Sparta and Masicka heats up&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Dancehall war season is in full swing, with the feud between &lt;strong&gt;Tommy Lee Sparta&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Masicka&lt;/strong&gt; now entering its second week and showing no signs of slowing down. The exchanges have been fierce, tactical and deeply personal, with both artists pushing the lyrical stakes higher each round.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Plus &lt;strong&gt;Chronic Law&lt;/strong&gt; returns with &lt;strong&gt;Badness Upgrade 2.0&lt;/strong&gt; - the sequel to &lt;em&gt;Badness Upgrade&lt;/em&gt; and one of the biggest tunes of the year on Riddim Yard in 2023.&lt;/p&gt;
